title: Definitions
context: PART III. SPECIAL PROCEEDINGS RELATING TO PUBLIC PROPERTY ยง101-51 Definitions. As used herein: &ldquo;Public property&rdquo; means real property (1) owned by a political subdivision of the State or (2) owned by the State in its own right and not owned by the United States. &ldquo;Public property&rdquo; shall not be deemed to include public lands, defined to be such by section 171-2.
